<field_public_text>:
Interrupt signal for each Slot      

These status bits indicate the logical OR of Interrupt signal and Wakeup signal for each slot. A maximum of 8 slots can be defined. If one interrupt signal is associated with multiple slots, the Host
Driver can identify the interrupt that is generated by reading these bits. By a power on reset or by setting Software Reset For All bit, the interrupt signals are deasserted and this status reads 00h.
 - Bit 00: Slot 1
 - Bit 01: Slot 2
 - Bit 02: Slot 3
 - .......... 
 - .......... 
 - Bit 07: Slot 8

 Note: MSHC Host Controller support single card slot. This register shall always return 0.
